From Matt A Telles Subject Re Required File format of WORD for MS WINDOW File In article cosmos writes Hi I am trying to develop a utility to view WORD for window But to do that I need to know the format of the DOC word for window file format anybody tell me what is the format of DOC file or direct me where can I get Or is it proprietory format Your help is greatly Thanks The format for Word for Windows doc files is available from Call their Developer Support Services number sorry don't have it handy and ask for the Word for Windows binary file format Warning It is not terribly useful and you will need to do a lot of looking before you can figure out how the stuff is General primer Word for Windows stores its data in two The first chunk is the actual text in the This is all stored together and has nothing but text and The second chunk is the formatting For general use to read a Word for Windows file skip the first bytes of the file its a general header Then read the remaining text until you hit binary Matt